LibreOffice Online docker

This directory contains everything needed to compile a
working docker container with LibreOffice Online.

Docker image can be built from packages or from source code.

All docker images built from this directory can be run with a TZ environment variable
to set the server timezone to something other than UTC.

Examples:

1. Build latest CODE based on Ubuntu 18.04 LTS

  cd from-packages
  docker build --no-cache -t mydomain/code -f Ubuntu .

2. Build LibreOffice Online 21.11 based on Ubuntu 18.04 LTS

  cd from-packages
  # Get your secret URL key from https://support.collaboraoffice.com/ (Collabora Partners/Customers)
  docker build --no-cache --build-arg type=lool --build-arg secret_key=<....> -t mydomain/lool -f Ubuntu .

3. Build LibreOffice Online 21.11 based on RHEL8

  cd from-packages
  # Get your secret URL key from https://support.collaboraoffice.com/ (Collabora Partners/Customers)
  docker build --no-cache --build-arg type=lool --build-arg secret_key=<....> -t mydomain/lool -f RHEL8 .

4. Build LibreOffice Online 21.11 license key enabled version based on Ubuntu 18.04 LTS

   cd from-packages
   docker build --no-cache --build-arg type=key -t mydomain/lool -f Ubuntu .

5. Build LibreOffice Online from master branch (from source code)

   cd from-source
   ./build.sh

Check build.sh for more build options!
